<div style="color:#414141; font-size:20px; margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 8px">'''>> Unknown Entities'''</div></div>

'''Level 775''' is the 776<sup>th</sup> level of the Backrooms.
=<div style="background-color:rgba(0,0,0,0.5); color: white; margin:1em;padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;">Description</div>=

<div class="right-image">
[[File:775-1.jpeg]]
A signed image of Level 775
</div>

‌'''Level 775''', also known as "The Dark Cage," presents a dim, lifeless urban landscape. This level experiences no day-night cycle and remains in perpetual darkness, with neither a moon nor stars visible in the sky. The temperature is consistently between -9°C (15.8°F) and 4°C (39.2°F), so wanderers must wear heavy clothing when traversing this area. Notably, no precipitation such as rain or snow occurs—only an eternal, dense fog fills the air.‌

‌The city within '''Level 775''' is enclosed by a massive transparent dome-like structure. Strangely, the exterior view beyond this structure is obscured by mosaic-like patterns, making it impossible to discern what lies outside. Additionally, the material used in this massive transparent dome-like structure does not belong to any known substance previously utilized in [[The Frontrooms]] and exhibits extremely high resilience, making it nearly indestructible or impossible to damage easily.‌

<div class="right-image">
[[File:775-2.jpeg]]
interior structure‌ of Level 775
</div>


The buildings within '''Level 775''' are predominantly high-rise residential structures, occupying the vast majority of the area, though a small number of low-rise residential buildings are also scattered throughout. Additionally, all construction materials used in this level’s buildings possess excellent soundproofing properties; however, the exact origin of these materials remains unknown, and all attempts using known techniques have failed to damage them.‌

‌Most exterior surfaces of buildings in '''Level 775''' are equipped with lighting fixtures, creating a brightly lit appearance from the outside. Surprisingly, however, the interior spaces remain pitch black, lacking any necessary illumination.

‌No electrical wiring or power infrastructure exists within '''Level 775''', yet all streetlights and electric-dependent devices operate normally without interruption. This phenomenon is highly unusual, defying conventional logic of power supply, and remains under detailed investigation—its origin still unexplained.‌

‌All buildings in '''Level 775''' are furnished with essential furniture and simple interior decoration. Strikingly, despite the presence of installed light fixtures meant for illumination, none appear to have switches or buttons to turn them on. Furthermore, some high-rise and low-rise residential buildings are vacant, seemingly abandoned for a long time. Typically, such unused spaces would accumulate spiderwebs in corners and crevices.‌

When wanderers in '''Level 775''' spend prolonged periods contemplating plans to escape this oppressive environment, their thoughts of fleeing the level or the Backrooms appear to be erased by an invisible force. Whenever they try to retain these ideas as guidance for escape, they find the notions fading from their minds like morning mist, leaving no tangible trace. This forgetting is not mere memory loss, but a deep, systematic erasure of the very will to escape—rendering wanderers unable to transform their innermost longing for freedom into actionable blueprints. Moreover, as wanderers persistently imagine escaping '''Level 775''' or the Backrooms over time, their memories gradually shift: from trivial daily details to significant moments like birthdays and holidays. And when such memories are written down, the text vanishes suddenly, in the blink of an eye.‌

=<div style="background-color:rgba(0,0,0,0.5); color: white; margin:1em;padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;">Outposts, Bases and Colonies</div>=

There are no known outposts, bases and colonies within '''Level 775'''

