<div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox">Additional Information:</span><br><center> ''Appendix: An Email from Level 775'' <br /><br />
</center>

<div class="right-image">
[[File:775-1.jpeg]]
The Cage
</div>

''We once tried to break free from the Backrooms’ cage-like grip, but unfortunately, our attempts failed. Trapped within this silent, shadowed city, I am confined inside an invisible, transparent cubic cell—a "boundary prison" I cannot cross or break. Yet it constantly presses upon me. Inside this airless cell, my thoughts are imprisoned, and my words are tightly restrained. I have no freedom.‌''

‌''Worse still, every attempt to escape has ended in failure. My mind feels locked, my memories quietly stolen and hidden away in some unknown, mysterious corner. This helplessness and fear hangs over my soul like a dark cloud, leaving me deeply confused and lost.‌''

‌''These imperceptible, intangible restraints weave through the Backrooms like a tangled maze, binding and entangling its levels in chaos, forming insurmountable barriers. They blur spatial boundaries and erect deep mental walls, severely blocking every effort to find and walk the path out of this enclosed realm. This cycle of failure and disorder makes the already unpredictable Backrooms even more unfathomable. We must now face not only overlapping, interwoven levels, but also the unknown dangers and challenges they bring. Hope of escape grows ever dimmer.‌''

‌''We have already failed.‌''

</div>

